The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                              Tuesday , November 3 , 2009                                                                                                                                                                                              Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Nov. 2: The National Stock Exchange and the Bombay Stock Exchange are likely to extend the trading time by two and a half hours from next month and a formal notification to this effect is expected shortly. Both the exchanges have discussed the issue (extension of trade timings) and a formal notification is expected shortly, a senior exchange official said. Market regulator Sebi has approved the extension of the trading time from 9 am to 5 pm.                            
	 New Delhi, Nov. 2: Finance minister Pranab Mukherjee would interact with economic editors tomorrow and provide them a comprehensive view of the overall economy. The two-day conference assumes significance at a time when the global slowdown has pulled down Indias growth to 6.7 per cent during 2008-09 from about 9 per cent a year ago.                            
	 Detroit, Nov. 2: Ford Motor surprised Wall Street with a quarterly profit on Monday and raised its 2011 outlook to solidly profitable, sending its shares up 5.7 per cent in pre-market trading. Cost cuts, improved credit results and increased market share in North America and other key areas have boosted growth.                            
	 New Delhi, Nov. 2: The Comptroller and Auditor General has constituted a team for auditing Reliance Industries expenses on eastern offshore KG-D6 fields and the exercise will begin this month.                             
	 New Delhi, Nov. 2: ICICI Bank CEO Chanda Kochhar has said the lender will consider rewarding its employees with bonus, which it skipped last year on account of poor performance. ICICI Bank has about 36,000 employees and would increase the headcount as it opens 580 branches this year.                            
	 Calcutta, Nov. 2: Punkaj Kumar Bajaj has taken over as the new managing director of SAILs Durgapur Steel Plant with effect from November 1. He has replaced V. Shyamsundar.                             
	 Mumbai, Nov. 2: The BSE, the NSE , forex, money and oil and oilseeds market remained closed today on account of Guru Nanak Jayanti.
                                                                                                                           
